text: Kosmos 305 ( meaning Cosmos 305) (Ye-8-5 series) was the fifth Soviet attempt at an unmanned lunar sample return. It was probably similar in design to the Luna 16 spacecraft. It was launched, on a Proton rocket, on October 22, 1969. The engines on the Block D upper stage failed, terminating the mission. This left the spacecraft stranded in Earth orbit. ==External links== * Zarya - Luna programme chronology Category:Luna program Category:Kosmos satellites Category:Sample return missions Category:Missions to the Moon Category:Spacecraft launched in 1969
